<div class="block">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="block__content">
      <p>It is important that your volunteers are trained to support vulnerable people with a variety of needs.  Being well trained gives protection to both volunteers and the people you support.<p>
      <p>Courses are frequently updated, so please check back regularly.</p>
      <article class="training-course">
        <h2 class="h2">Safeguarding</h2>
        <p>A half day training course on safeguarding adults for Manchester based organisations, providing an understanding of the mental capacity act (MCA). This training takes place at regular intervals at the MACC office on Swan Street in Central Manchester.</p>
        <h3 class="h3">How to book</h3>
        <p>Find out more about safeguarding courses here: <a href="https://www.manchestercommunitycentral.org/support-groups/training#unnamed_filter=.safeguarding">Safeguarding courses information</a></p>
      </article>
      <article class="training-course">
        <h2 class="h2">Volunteering and the law</h2>
        <p>A full day training course covering all aspects of volunteering for Manchester based organisations. This training takes place at the MACC office on Swan Street in Central Manchester. Content includes volunteers rights, health & safety, vetting & criminal records checks, insurances, restrictions on volunteering, contracts or agreements, volunteering & welfare benefits, and policies for successfully involving volunteers.</p>
        <h3 class="h3">How to book</h3>
        <p>Find out more about the MACC courses for volunteers here: <a href="https://www.manchestercommunitycentral.org/support-groups/training#unnamed_filter=.volunteering">Volunteering courses information</a></p>
      </article>
      <article class="training-course">
        <h2 class="h2">Self defense and conflict resolution</h2>
        <p>We can organise this course through Rachel Cruz on request.</p>
        <h3 class="h3">How to book</h3>
        <p>Please <a href="get-in-touch">get in touch</a> for more information.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="training-course">
        <h2 class="h2">Volunteer DBS checks</h2>
        <p>Salford CVS provide DBS checks for &pound;18 on request.</p>
        <h3 class="h3">How to book</h3>
        <p>Information to follow.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="training-course">
        <h2 class="h2">Online Courses</h2>
        <p>There are a wide range of online courses available, including safeguarding, health and safety and conflict resolution. Standard courses are &pound;1 and we have secured a reduced rate of 50p for any courses for groups working towards the best practice awards.</p>
        <h3 class="h3">How to book</h3>
        <p>You can book onto any of the online courses run by Psittacus at <a href="https://www.psittacus-ble.co.uk">psittacus-ble.co.uk</a></p>
      </article>
      <p>Volunteers will also benefit from training which develops their understanding of the challenges faced by people who are homeless, and builds their knowledge of other organisations and services.</p>
